Sorcery: Shadows under Llylgamyn
Copyright (C) 2021 Dave Moore

Linux Instructions (Ubuntu 20:04 LTS):

Make sure the following packages/third-party libraries from the Standard and
Universe Repositories are installed:

- libsfml-dev (2.5.1+dfsg-1build1)
- libsfml-doc (2.5.1+dfsg-1build1)
- libsqlite3-0 (3.31.1-4)
- libsqlite3-dev (3.31.1-4)
- libjsoncpp-dev (1.7.4-3.1ubuntu2)
- doxygen (1.8.17-0ubuntu2)
- libfmt-dev (6.1.2+ds-2)
- uuid-dev (2.34-0.1ubuntu9.1)
- binutils-dev (2.34-6ubuntu1.1)
- libunwind-dev (1.2.1-9build1)
- yasm (1.3.0-2ubuntu1)

Add the following repository:

ppa:texus/tgui-0.8

And then install the following additional package:

libtgui-dev (0.8.9+focal)

Download, compile and install the following libraries (cmake needed):

- sfeMovie https://github.com/Yalir/sfeMovie (commit 698ccf2)
- Thor https://github.com/Bromeon/Thor (commit f9b7890)

Then make sure the following header libraries are included and linked (default
location to install them - as specified in the env/.mk files - are in
subdirectories in the inc folder):

- simpleini https://github.com/brofield/simpleini/
- sqlite modern cpp wrapper https://github.com/SqliteModernCpp/sqlite_modern_cpp
- Magic Enum C++ https://github.com/Neargye/magic_enum
- Backward-cpp https://github.com/bombela/backward-cpp
- cereal https://github.com/USCiLab/cereal
- tgui-nanogui-theme https://gitlab.com/rubenwardy/tgui-nanogui-theme

Both CMake (via VSCode/CMakeTools) and Code::Blocks are supported.

Additional support tools useful for development:

- Build EAR https://github.com/rizsotto/Bear

Note that to compile Sorcery: Shadows under Llylgamyn requires a compiler
with C++20 support such as g++10.3.

